d priority\n- Failed tasks remain in failed state when retries exhausted\n\n#### Phase 6: Dead Letter Queue (`/workspace/phases/phase-06.md`)\n- Move permanently-failed tasks to dead letter queue (DLQ)\n- View all dead-lettered tasks for a queue\n- Dead-lettered tasks retain error info and failure count\n- Move dead-lettered tasks back to original queue for fresh retries\n- Clear all dead-lettered tasks for a queue\n- Each queue has independent DLQ\n\n#### Phase 7: Task Dependencies (`/workspace/phases/phase-07.md`)\n- Tasks can declare dependencies on other task IDs\n- Dependent tasks blocked until dependencies complete\n- Check for circular dependencies at task-creation time\n- Depending on non-existent task causes error\n- Failed dependency does NOT fail dependents (they remain blocked)\n- Inspect task dependency status\n\n#### Phase 8: Concurrency Control (`/workspace/phases/phase-08.md`)\n- Per-queue max concurrency setting\n- Limit how many tasks can be in \"processing\" state simultaneously\n- Reaching limit returns null even if pending tasks available\n- Completing/failing a task frees a slot\n- Default: unlimited concurrency\n- Set and query concurrency limit and active count\n- Interacts correctly with priority ordering\n\n#### Phase 9: Progress Tracking and Cancellation (`/workspace/phases/phase-09.md`)\n- Processing tasks report progress (0-100%) with optional message\n- Query task's current progress\n- Subscribe to progress updates with listener pattern\n- Unsubscribe from progress updates\n- Cancel pending or processing tasks\n- Cancelled pending tasks removed from queue\n- Cancelled processing tasks updated accordingly\n- Cancelled tasks never retried\n\n#### Phase 10: Recurring Tasks (`/workspace/phases/phase-10.md`)\n- Schedule associates cron expression with queue and task template\n- Simple cron subset:\n  - `*/N * * * *` – every N minutes\n  - `0 * * * *` – every hour on the hour\n  - `0 0 * * *` – every day at midnight\n- Create, remove, list active schedules\n- Manual \"tick\" mechanism to evaluate and enqueue due tasks\n- Once enqueued, recurring tasks are regular tasks\n- Removing schedule stops future occurrences\n\n#### Phase 11: Middleware Pipeline (`/workspace/phases/phase-11.md`)\n- Register middleware functions per queue\n- Task passes through all middleware in order before handler\n- Middleware receives task and \"next\" function\n- Not calling \"next\" skips remaining processing\n- Middleware can modify task\n- Middleware errors mark task as failed\n- Per-queue processing handler invoked after middleware\n- Each queue has independent middleware stack\n\n#### Phase 12: Graceful Shutdown (`/workspace/phases/phase-12.md`)\n- Shutdown stops accepting new tasks\n- Attempting to add tasks during shutdown errors\n- Wait for processing tasks with configurable timeout\n- Force-cancel tasks exceeding timeout\n- Register callbacks to run during shutdown\n- Shutdown summary: completed, force-cancelled, duration\n- Multiple shutdown calls safe (return same result)\n- Complete immediately if no processing tasks\n\n### 5. Files in src/\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/src/`\n\nCurrently contains **only:**\n- `.gitkeep` (empty marker file)\n\n**Note:** The `src/` directory is empty and ready for implementation. The main API should be exported from `src/index.ts`.\n\n### 6. Test Files\n\n**Status:** No test files currently exist\n\nThe project is set up with:\n- **Test Framework:** Vitest 2.0.0\n- **Configuration:** `/workspace/vitest.config.ts`\n  - Global test functions enabled\n  - Test timeout: 10 seconds\n- **Run Tests:** `npm run test`\n\nNo `.test.ts`, `.spec.ts`, or test files exist yet. Tests need to be written as implementation progresses.\n\n### 7. Additional Configuration Files\n\n**ESLint Configuration** (`/workspace/.eslintrc.cjs`):\n- Parser: @typescript-eslint/parser\n- Extends: eslint:recommended + typescript-eslint\n- ES2022 target\n- Node environment\n- Rule: Unused vars with argsIgnorePattern `^_